|Lyrics|Placement:Bottom|Align:Standard Rules|Offset:0
|Lyric1|Text:"Y’ say you ain’t no thief\nBut you keep the fund\nThe gov gave you by ac-ci-dent\n\nY’ say that she’s a whore\nBut in your head\nYou sure-ly sleep with an-y lad.\n\nWe ain’t good or bad, my friend\nWe’re op-por-tu-nists till the end\nUn-til the bill comes due\nhold on, hold on.\n\nWhen you roll a six\nYou have your-self to thank for it.\n\nSin-ging like a nun\nThere’s no tar-get like the in-no-cent.\n\nIn a-no-ther world\nThings won’t be much dif-fe-rent.\n\nWe ain’t good or bad, my friend\nWe’re op-por-tu-nists till the end\nUn-til the bill comes\n\nWe lead our-selves do-own\nOur mind is crushed by id-le hopes\nAnd we all stand by\nAnd we all stand by.\n\n_ _ _ _ _\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _\n_ _ _ _ _\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _\n_ _ _ _ _ _\n_ _ _\n\nWe ain’t good or bad, my friend\nWe’re hy-po-crites un-till the end\nUn-til the bill comes due\nhold on, hold on.\nI\'ll be there too\n"
